Some of the Comrades runners with members of the Panthers executive.Photo: supplied Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories THE Tongaat Panthers Athletic Club runners will be among the 2 000 athletes when they meet at the Durban City Hall to conquer the 92nd running of the Comrades Marathon on June 4. The Panthers met on Saturday, May 27, for the Chairman s Run, which took place from Basil Pillay s residence, one of the founder members of Tongaat Panthers Athletic Club. The runners also did their final run when they joined the Thinny s League Challenge last Sunday. The executive and members of Tongaat Panthers wish Comrades runners everything of the best and an injury- free run. - Supplied. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.